parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS) Hydraulic Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS hydraulic unit can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floorboard, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
grinding noise when braking
and the ABS warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailable recall repair can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives a recall notification
but the repair is delayed or unavailable
and the vehicle remains in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to inadequate protection in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminate
airbags fail to deploy
or deploy incorrectly
passenger seat airbag is disabled
SRS light comes on
warning indicator for unbuckled passenger appears despite the passenger being buckled up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dashboard defect can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to inadequate protection in the event of a crash, and increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Dashboard starts popping apart
dashboard splits apart at the seam
particularly on the passenger side in front of the airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition switch defect can cause the vehicle to be driven without the transmission being in park, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Key can be removed from the column without the car being in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to hesitate or fail to respond, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes hesitate to respond
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine, head gasket, and other components, which can result in costly repairs and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: White fumes emitting from the hood
unknown warning indicators illuminating
the engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing inconvenience or safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the starter motor fails to engage.
